    • decrypt

      public byte[] decrypt​(java.security.PrivateKey key, byte[] ciphertext) throws java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException, javax.crypto.NoSuchPaddingException, java.security.InvalidKeyException, javax.crypto.IllegalBlockSizeException, javax.crypto.BadPaddingException
      Decrypts an encrypted statement using RSA cipher.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to use to decrypt
      ciphertext - the text in bytes to decrypt
      Returns:
      the decrypted array of bytes
      Throws:
      java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if "RSA/ECB/OAEPWithSHA1AndMGF1Padding" is not an usable algorithm
      java.security.InvalidKeyException - if signer can't use the given key to sign or verify
      javax.crypto.NoSuchPaddingException - if padding is wrong
      javax.crypto.BadPaddingException - if padding is wrong
      javax.crypto.IllegalBlockSizeException - if block size is wrong

    • searchByKey

      public void searchByKey​(java.security.PrivateKey key, java.security.KeyStore ks) throws java.security.KeyStoreException, java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException, java.security.SignatureException, java.security.InvalidKeyException
      Searches in the KeyStore given for a possible match for keys with the given private key.
      Parameters:
      key - the private key we look a matching key for
      ks - the KeyStore from which we use Certificate entries.
      Throws:
      java.security.KeyStoreException - if there is a problem in the KeyStore with aliases
      java.security.InvalidKeyException - if signer can't use the given key to sign or verify
      java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if an usable algorithm is used
      java.security.SignatureException - if signer can't sign the message

    • validDSAKeyPair

      public boolean validDSAKeyPair​(java.security.interfaces.DSAPrivateKey privateKey, java.security.interfaces.DSAPublicKey pubKey) throws java.security.InvalidKeyException, java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException, java.security.SignatureException
      Checks if an DSA key pair matches. Signs a test message using the private key and verify it using the public key.
      Parameters:
      privateKey - the private key of the key pair
      pubKey - the public key of the key pair
      Returns:
      true if keys match, false if not
      Throws:
      java.security.InvalidKeyException - if signer can't use the given key to sign or verify
      java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if "SHA256withDSA" isn't an usable algorithm
      java.security.SignatureException - if signer can't sign the message

    • searchMatchCertificateAndKeys

      public void searchMatchCertificateAndKeys​(java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,​java.security.PrivateKey> keys, java.security.cert.X509Certificate certificate) throws java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException, java.security.InvalidKeyException, java.security.SignatureException
      Given the public key's algorithm from the certificate, searches in the keys map if algorithm, and key pair match. If a key pair is found, shows it.
      Parameters:
      keys - a TreeMap of PrivateKey with the corresponding file name
      certificate - the certificate in which we look for a key
      Throws:
      java.security.InvalidKeyException - if signer can't use the given key to sign or verify
      java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if "SHA256withDSA" isn't an usable algorithm
